# TypeScript Tsconfig Inheritance Context

## Rules

- Every package-level `tsconfig.json` must extend the repository root `./tsconfig.json` using the correct relative path from the package location (for example `../../tsconfig.json` or `../../../tsconfig.json`).
- Shared TypeScript compiler options must be defined only in the root `./tsconfig.json`.
- Package-level `tsconfig.json` files may define only local overrides such as `rootDir`, `outDir`, `baseUrl`, `paths`, `include`, and `exclude`.
- Do not duplicate base compiler options across package tsconfig files.
- Every package-level `tsconfig.json` must define the local alias `@src/*` with this exact mapping:

```json
"paths": {
  "@src/*": ["./src/*"]
}
```

## Example

```json
{
  "extends": "../../tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "paths": {
      "@src/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules", "dist"]
}
```

Example for nested library directories (for example `./packages/logger/some-submodule`):

```json
{
  "extends": "../../../tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "paths": {
      "@src/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules", "dist"]
}
```
